    "recap_headline": "Fresno State Athletics",
    "recap_text": "FRESNO, Calif.\n\u2013 Fresno State Bulldogs baseball fell to Nevada Wolf Pack baseball, 9\u20134, on Sunday afternoon at Pete\u00a0Beiden\u00a0Field at Bob Bennett Stadium, as Nevada completed the three-game Mountain West sweep.\nWith the loss, Fresno State dropped to 7\u201311 overall and 0\u20133 in conference play, while Nevada improved to 11\u20136 and 3\u20130 in the Mountain West.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nNevada struck first in the opening inning with an RBI single from Shintaro Matsuzaki to take a 1\u20130 lead. Fresno State answered immediately in the bottom half when Michael Boyd grounded out to first base, bringing home\nJett Ruby\nto tie the game at one.\nThe Wolf Pack regained control in the second inning on a two-run home run from Lucas Waller, pushing Nevada ahead 3\u20131. Fresno State battled back in the third. Boyd led off with a double, and\nSky Collins\nfollowed with a walk before\nCam Schneider\nripped a double down the left-field line to score both runners and even the score at 3\u20133.\nNevada broke the game open in the fourth inning. After two runners reached, Trenton Dobie delivered a three-run double to left field to give the Wolf Pack a 6\u20133 advantage. Nevada added insurance runs later in the game, including a sacrifice fly in the sixth and solo home runs from Austin Doyle in the seventh and ninth innings.\nFresno State picked up its final run in the eighth inning when\nAustin Young\nscored on a wild pitch after\nOwen Faust\nsingled and advanced into scoring position. The Bulldogs were unable to mount a late rally, as Nevada closer Eric Valdez shut the door over the final three innings.\nNOTES\nOwen Faust\nled Fresno State with two hits.\nCam Schneider\ndrove in two runs with a double in the third inning.\nMichael Boyd doubled and recorded an RBI.\nSky Collins\nreached base three times and stole a base.\nUP NEXT\nThe Bulldogs will be back at Pete Beiden Field at Bob Bennett Stadium on Tuesday to host CSUN at 6:05 p.m. PT."
